package assignment3;

public class ProtectedTest {
	
	protected void sweetHome()
	{
		System.out.println("My Sweet Home");
	}

}



package assignment4;

import assignment3.ProtectedTest;

public class ProtectedMethodInDifferentPackage {
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		
		 new Acess().printHome();
		
	}
	
}

class Acess extends ProtectedTest 
{
	void printHome()
	{
		sweetHome();
	}
}


output
My Sweet Home


Explanation:
protected access modifier allows our subclasses to be outside our superclass package and yet still inherit pieces of the class including 
methods and constructors.. 
The only way the subclass can access the protected methods is by inheritance
